text: Warren County is a county in the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2020 census, the population was 134,554, making it the fifth-most populous county in Kentucky. Its county seat is Bowling Green. Warren County is included in the Bowling Green, KY Metropolitan Statistical Area. It is in the Pennyroyal Plateau and Western Coal Fields regions. == References == Category:1790s establishments in Kentucky Category:1796 establishments in the United States Category:Kentucky counties
